<h2 id="editors-notes">Editorâ€™s notes</h2>

<p>Hereâ€™s three quick trio of exercises you can play, all of which are using triads for the chords of A, D, and E. Focused only on the thinnest 3 strings, I quite enjoy exploring how I can put these mini chord shapes together to come up with something fun. Tabs for each exercise are below, and be sure to check out the charts &amp; tabs Iâ€™ve written up in order to grok how these triad shapes can in fact be used up &amp; down the fretboard. I hope you enjoy! - David Potsiadlo (March 29, 2019)</p>

